        "payload": "tree f0a5406b8aec89b3546b9d342bc0d8f50040022f\nparent bd0287d650c24dc41e0362675a9f6a49ee952def\nauthor Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1782316058 -0700\ncommitter Lőrinc <pap.lorinc@gmail.com> 1782321866 -0700\n\ntest: avoid scratch free warning\n\nThe scratch test intentionally passes a badly initialized scratch space to the error paths.\nIt used a zeroed stack object for that input.\n\nGCC 17 snapshot can inline `secp256k1_scratch_space_destroy` and warn that `free()` may be called on that stack object.\nThe invalid-magic path returns before `free()`, but the gcc-snapshot CI job uses `-Werror`, so the warning breaks the build.\n\nZero the existing heap-allocated scratch object before the invalid-input checks instead.\nThis keeps the same badly initialized scratch-space coverage while making the pointer provenance match the possible `free()` target.\n",
